[33mcommit ff5c9e44e584bfa24f0eef20bd3a467a1fd84f94[m
Author: kmka330 <163684193+kmka330@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 13 23:45:05 2025 +0200

    Implement secure network client and refactor admin UI
    
    Architectural Refactoring
    
    Refactored the Admin Panel from a direct-access application into a proper network client (AdminClient.java) that connects to the server via sockets.
    Created a new com.whispr.securechat.admin package to cleanly separate the admin module from the server and the main chat client logic.
    UI Simplification
    
    Replaced MaterialFX components with standard JavaFX controls (Button, ListView) to ensure functionality and simplify the UI ahead of the deadline.
    Removed MaterialFX theme loading from AdminApplication to resolve configuration issues.
    Security Implementation (Client & Server)
    
    Implemented a full, two-step secure handshake protocol for the admin session, mirroring the main client's security design.
    AdminClient:
    Generates its own RSA key pair upon creation.
    Proactively sends its public RSA key to the server to initiate the key exchange.
    Receives the server's public RSA key.
    Generates a secret AES session key, encrypts it with the server's public RSA key, and sends it to the server.
    ClientHandler (Server-side):
    Added logic to handle AES_KEY_EXCHANGE messages.
    Uses the server's private RSA key to decrypt the incoming AES key.
    Stores the decrypted AES session key for secure communication throughout the admin's session.

